@startuml SafeTransfer Use Cases
title SafeTransfer - Main Use Cases

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false

actor "API Client" as Client
actor "Operations / Monitoring" as Ops
actor "Kafka Consumer\n(Audit Listener)" as KafkaConsumer

rectangle "SafeTransfer" {
  usecase "Create Wallet" as UC_CreateWallet
  usecase "Get Wallet" as UC_GetWallet
  usecase "Get Balance" as UC_GetBalance
  usecase "Deposit Money" as UC_Deposit
  usecase "Create Transfer" as UC_Transfer
  usecase "Get Transfer" as UC_GetTransfer
  usecase "Retry Outbox Publishing" as UC_Outbox
  usecase "Publish Transfer Event" as UC_Publish
  usecase "Record Audit Event" as UC_Audit
  usecase "Expose Metrics" as UC_Metrics
}

Client --> UC_CreateWallet
Client --> UC_GetWallet
Client --> UC_GetBalance
Client --> UC_Deposit
Client --> UC_Transfer
Client --> UC_GetTransfer

UC_Transfer .> UC_GetBalance : validates funds
UC_Transfer .> UC_Publish : creates outbox event
UC_Outbox .> UC_Publish : dispatches event
UC_Publish .> UC_Audit : consumed asynchronously

KafkaConsumer --> UC_Audit
Ops --> UC_Metrics
Ops --> UC_Outbox

note bottom of UC_Transfer
  Transfer is idempotent by tenant + idempotency key.
  Reusing the same key returns the existing transfer.
end note

note bottom of UC_GetBalance
  Balance is calculated from ledger entries.
end note

@enduml
